[SN]TITLE[SN]
Michael McCabe admits punching moving car in Leicester

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 37-year-old man who jumped on a moving car and punched its windscreen has pleaded guilty to racially aggravated criminal damage, damaging motor vehicles and resisting arrest.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Michael McCabe, of Kirk Lodge, London Road, Leicester, will be sentenced on 30 August.
Mobile phone footage shared on social media showed him damaging cars on Burleys Way in Leicester.
The attacks took place during afternoon rush hour last Thursday.
